  <span>Unable to tear themselves away, hazel eyes continue to stay on Alyssa, on the way the corners of her lips are turning up slightly, on the few strands of her falling into her face. She reaches forward before she can stop herself, she brushes the hair out of the way, looking away for barely a second. </span>
